A chair without a back or arm rests is a '''stool''',<ref>{{cite web|url = http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/stool+?s=t|title = Stool|publisher = Dictionary.com|accessdate = 2012-05-13}}</ref> or when raised up, a bar stool.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.thefreedictionary.com/barstool|title = Bar Stool|publisher = The Free Dictionary By Farlex|accessdate = 2012-05-13}}</ref> A chair with arms is an '''armchair'''<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.thefreedictionary.com/armchair|title = Armchair|publisher = The Free Dictionary By Farlex|accessdate = 2012-05-13}}</ref> and with folding action and reclining footrest, a recliner.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/recliner+?s=t|title = Recliner|publisher = Dictionary.com|accessdate = 2012-05-13}}</ref> A permanently fixed chair in a train or theater is a '''seat'''<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.thefreedictionary.com/seat|title = Seat|publisher = The Free Dictionary By Farlex|accessdate = 2012-05-13}}</ref> or, in an airplane, airline seat;<ref>{{cite web|url = http://encyclopedia.thefreedictionary.com/airline+seat|title = Airline seat|publisher = The Free Dictionary By Farlex|accessdate = 2012-05-13}}</ref> when riding, it is a saddle<ref>{{cite web|url = http://encyclopedia.thefreedictionary.com/saddle|title = Saddle|publisher = The Free Dictionary By Farlex|accessdate = 2012-05-13}}</ref> and bicycle saddle,<ref>{{cite web|url = http://encyclopedia.thefreedictionary.com/bicycle+saddle|title = Bicycle saddle|publisher = The Free Dictionary By Farlex|accessdate = 2012-05-13}}</ref> and for an automobile, a car seat<ref>{{cite web|url = http://encyclopedia.thefreedictionary.com/car+seat|title = Carseat|publisher = The Free Dictionary By Farlex|accessdate = 2012-05-13}}</ref> or infant car seat.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://encyclopedia.thefreedictionary.com/infant+car+seat|title = Infant carseat|publisher = The Free Dictionary By Farlex|accessdate = 2012-05-13}}</ref>  With wheels it is a wheelchair<ref>{{cite web|url = http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/wheelchair?fromAsk=true&o=100074|title = Wheelchair|publisher = Dictionary.com|accessdate = 2012-05-13}}</ref> and when hung from above, a swing.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://encyclopedia.thefreedictionary.com/swing|title = Swing|publisher = The Free Dictionary By Farlex|accessdate = 2012-05-13}}</ref>

